14/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski said on Wednesday (December 13th) that Kosovo poses no current threat to Macedonia's national security or territorial integrity. He acknowledged however that certain risks could arise, following the outcome of the status settlement process. His comments followed a visit to the Macedonian Intelligence Agency's headquarters and talks with officials there. (Vecer - 14/12/06; Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 13/12/06)
